.TH ESLINT-CONFIG "1" "December 2025" "eslint-config 202208062255-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
eslint-config \- Interactive ESLint and Prettier configuration generator for JavaScript/React projects
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B eslint-config
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B eslint-config
is an interactive setup wizard that creates standardized ESLint and Prettier configuration files for JavaScript and React projects. It follows Airbnb's JavaScript Style Guide and integrates ESLint with Prettier for consistent code formatting.
.PP
The script installs necessary npm packages, prompts for configuration preferences (package manager, file format, line length, trailing commas), generates .eslintrc and .prettierrc files with best-practice rules, and configures React Hooks linting.
.PP
eslint-config simplifies project setup by automating the installation and configuration of ESLint, Prettier, and all required plugins/parsers with opinionated defaults that work out of the box.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B eslint-config
Run interactive setup wizard in current directory (default)
.TP
.B eslint-config --dir /path/to/project
Run setup wizard in specified project directory
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.TP
.BR \-\-silent
Suppress non-essential output messages
.TP
.BR \-\-dir " " \fI\,DIRECTORY\/\fR
Set project directory for configuration files (default: current directory)
.SH USAGE
.B eslint-config
.PP
Runs interactive setup wizard in current directory. Prompts for package manager, file format, and preferences.
.PP
.B eslint-config --dir ~/projects/my-app
.PP
Runs setup wizard in specified project directory.
.SH INTERACTIVE PROMPTS
The script presents five configuration prompts:
.SS 1. Package Manager Selection
.RS
.EX
Which package manager are you using?
1) Yarn
2) npm
3) Cancel
.EE
.RE
.PP
Selects installation command:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Yarn: Uses `yarn add` for package installation
.IP \(bu 2
npm: Uses `npm install` for package installation
.IP \(bu 2
Validates package manager is installed before proceeding
.RE
.SS 2. Configuration File Format
.RS
.EX
Which ESLint and Prettier configuration format do you prefer?
1) .js
2) .json
3) Cancel
.EE
.RE
.PP
Configuration format options:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
.js: JavaScript module (module.exports = {...})
.IP \(bu 2
.json: JSON format ({...})
.IP \(bu 2
Determines file extension for .eslintrc and .prettierrc
.RE
.SS 3. Max Line Length
.RS
.EX
What max line length do you want to set for ESLint and Prettier?
(Recommendation: 80)
> 120
.EE
.RE
.PP
Line length configuration:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Default suggestion: 80 characters
.IP \(bu 2
Accepts: 2-3 digit numbers (e.g., 80, 100, 120, 150)
.IP \(bu 2
Used in Prettier printWidth setting
.IP \(bu 2
Enforced by ESLint max-len rule (currently disabled)
.RE
.SS 4. Trailing Commas Style
.RS
.EX
What style of trailing commas do you want to enforce with Prettier?
1) none
2) es5
3) all
.EE
.RE
.PP
Trailing comma options:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
none: No trailing commas anywhere
.IP \(bu 2
es5: Trailing commas where valid in ES5 (objects, arrays)
.IP \(bu 2
all: Trailing commas wherever possible (including function parameters)
.IP \(bu 2
See: https://prettier.io/docs/en/options.html#trailing-commas
.RE
.SS 5. Existing Config Files
If existing configuration files detected:
.RS
.EX
Existing ESLint config file(s) found: .eslintrc.json
Write .eslintrc.js (Y/n)?
.EE
.RE
.PP
Behavior:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Detects: .eslintrc*, .prettierrc*, prettier.config.js
.IP \(bu 2
Warns about configuration loading priority
.IP \(bu 2
Allows skipping generation if conflicts exist
.IP \(bu 2
User can choose to overwrite or skip
.RE
